entries.femaleVariant: Saw more of those weird murals.
Saw more of those freaky murals.
Did they start making sense? Tell any sort of story?
They're all tarot cards.
Maybe – hard to say.
All just a bunch of tarot cards.
Well, if they did, it was lost on me.
The tarot tells the story of a fool's journey. Show me what you found, I'll tell you what's left.
Pretty sure my brain's now beyond repair.
entries.maleVariant: I'm pretty sure my brain's now beyond repair.

entries.femaleVariant: Here.
Hm... You're still missing two arcana – Judgement and The Devil.
Thanks.
Thanks. Didn't get much out of that, but thanks.
entries.maleVariant: Thanks. Didn't get much of that, but thanks.

entries.femaleVariant: What's this Judgement about?
Rather not run into the Devil. Got a feelin' he's bad vibes.
What's up with the wandering fool?
What's Judgement represent?
The Devil doesn't sound good.
My guess is that they relate to a turning point in your life – one that's soon to arrive.
Tell me more about this fool's journey.
The fool is you and Silverhand.
You've traveled a long road together, discovered your potential.
Where're we headed?
Your destination is the World, the final arcanum. Both of you waged a war on the world, so there are two possibilities – declare victory or make peace.
Could lose the war, too.
Yes – unfortunately, that's true.
One possible future. Of redemption, transition, awakening.
The angel with the trumpet symbolizes the end of an era – and a call to rebirth, to a new beginning.
That's the card of primal, dormant desires, but also the will to survive.
Hm. Doesn't sound so bad, actually.
It also represents a false world – the trap these desires lay for you.
You'll understand when the time comes. I can't explain everything.
All the tarot can tell me is that you will reach the World by one of four paths.
Meaning?
The final leg of the journey goes through the Sun, the Star, Temperance or the Devil.
Could just die, not even get that far.
Oh, c'mon, you won't let that happen.
Take this. It's all I can do to help.
Good luck, V. On whatever road you choose.
[Take]
